{"ID":270365, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"365\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs364.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs366.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 365<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">Has the Gospel of the kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> commenced in the last days? And will God take it from the man\n  until He takes him Himself?<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> I have read it precisely as the words flowed from the lips of Jesus\n  Christ. John the Revelator saw an angel flying through the midst of heaven, having the everlasting\n  Gospel to preach unto them that dwell on the earth.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The scripture is ready to be fulfilled when great wars,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> famines, pestilence,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> great distress,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span>\n  judgments, &amp;c., are ready to be poured out on the inhabitants of the earth.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> John saw the angel\n  having the holy Priesthood, who should preach the everlasting Gospel to all nations.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> God had an\n  angel&mdash;a special messenger&mdash;ordained and prepared for that purpose in the last days. Woe, woe be\n  to that man or set of men who lift up their hands against God<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and His witness<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> in these last days:\n  for they shall deceive<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> almost the very chosen ones!<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Eternal Judgment<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">My enemies say that I <i>have<\/i> been a true prophet.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> Why, I had rather be a fallen true prophet than\n  a false prophet. When a man goes about prophesying, and commands men to obey his teachings, he\n  must either be a true or false prophet. False prophets<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> always arise to oppose the true prophets and\n  they will prophesy so very near the truth that they will deceive almost the very chosen ones.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The doctrine of eternal judgments<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> belongs to the first principles of the Gospel,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> in the last\n  days. In relation to the kingdom of God, the devil always sets up his kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> at the very same time\n  in opposition to God.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> Every man who has a calling to minister<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> to the inhabitants of the world<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span>\n  was ordained to that very purpose<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> in the Grand Council of heaven<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> before this world was.<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> I\n  suppose I was ordained to this very office in that Grand Council.<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> It is the testimony that I want that\n  I am God&rsquo;s servant,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and this people His people.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> The ancient prophets declared that in the last days\n  the God of heaven should set up a kingdom which should never be destroyed, nor left to other\n  people;<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> and the very time that was calculated on, this people were struggling to bring it out. He that\n  arms himself with gun, sword, or pistol, except in the defense of truth, will sometime be sorry for\n  it. I never carry any weapon with me bigger than my penknife. When I was dragged before<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113496\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113496)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113496)\">D&amp;C 27:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114250\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114250)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114250)\">D&amp;C 65:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114334\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114334)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114334)\">D&amp;C 71:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114644\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114644)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114644)\">D&amp;C 84:19,80,86<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115934\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115934)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115934)\">D&amp;C 124:19,130<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110808\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110808)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110808)\">Rev. 14:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114777\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114777)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114777)\">D&amp;C 87:1-8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116258\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116258)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116258)\">D&amp;C 130:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108200\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108200)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108200)\">Matt. 24:7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108575\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108575)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108575)\">Luke 21:23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117087\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclic